In this lab you will build a strong foundation in Python programming. You will learn Python syntax, data types, sequence containers, functions, modules, and Object-Oriented Programming through hands-on coding challenges. This prepares you for building backend web applications with Django in upcoming labs.

Learning Objectives
By the end of this lab, you will be able to:
- Understand Python syntax, variables, and basic data types (int, float, str, bool)
- Use conditional statements (if/elif/else) and comparison operators
- Implement loops (for and while) for iteration
- Work with sequence containers: lists, tuples, dictionaries, and sets
- Define and call functions with parameters, return values, and default arguments
- Organize code using modules and imports
- Apply Object-Oriented Programming: classes, objects, methods, and inheritance
- Follow the PEP 8 Style Guide for clean, readable code
